You are taking on the role of Park Ranger. Your strategies will be used by others in many places around the world to solve the litter problem. You have been equipped with AI powered cameras that issue Fixed Penalty Notices, as well as a team of litter-picking robot spiders. You have the task of solving ten stages of increasingly difficult litter situations in your park. To complete each stage you must splat all of the bugs with tickets and clear up all of the litter. If you are carrying some litter then you can splat bugs by delivering the ticket by hand (if you can catch them), but you most likely won't have time for that. You and your cameras can splat bugs by shooting tickets at them from a distance, which will be the most effective way to wipe them out before the situation gets out of control. Your advanced technology has limited uses per stage, so you must act quickly and strategically so that you don't have to manually pick up all the litter after the bugs have all inevitably been splatted out of existence. Also be very careful not to hit innocent bystanders with tickets, the cameras do not hit innocent bystanders as they have built-in facial recognition. It is up to you to save our beautiful world from becoming a wasteland! Good luck! 